articles.author: Stephanie Kelly
articles.description: Ousted OpenAI CEO Sam Altman and former President Greg Brockman joined executives at the company's San Francisco headquarters on Sunday after interim CEO Mira Murati told staff she invited Altman, The Information reported on Sunday.
articles.title: OpenAI invites Altman, Brockman to HQ:, The Information reports

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China left benchmark lending rates unchanged at a monthly fixing on Monday, matching expectations, as a weaker yuan continued to limit further monetary easing and policymakers waited to see the effects of previous stimulus on credit demand.
articles.title: China keeps lending benchmark rates unchanged, as expected

articles.author: Tetsushi Kajimoto, Kentaro Sugiyama
articles.description: Japan's big employers are set to follow this year's bumper pay hikes with another round in 2024, which are expected to help lift household spending and give the central bank the conditions it needs to finally roll back massive monetary stimulus.
articles.title: Japan's back-to-back wage bonanza would open door for BOJ exit

articles.author: Florence Tan
articles.description: Oil futures nudged higher on Monday, extending gains on expectations of OPEC+ deepening supply cuts to shore up prices, which have fallen for four weeks on easing concern of Mid-East supply disruption brought about by the Israel-Hamas conflict.
articles.title: Oil extends gains as OPEC+ to mull deeper cuts

articles.author: Himanshi Akhand
articles.description: Australian bourse operator ASX Ltd (ASX.AX) said on Monday it entered a deal with TATA Consultancy Services (TCS) to design and replace its trading, clearing and settlement system, after months of backlash since pulling a blockchain-based overhaul of the system last year.
articles.title: Australian bourse operator partners with TCS for long due trading software overhaul

articles.author: Scott Murdoch
articles.description: Westpac Banking Corp (WBC.AX), Australia's third largest bank by market capitalisation, said on Monday it would raise A$750 million ($488.1 million) in an Additional Tier 1 (AT1) capital transaction.
articles.title: Westpac to raise $488 million in additional Tier 1 capital

articles.author: Tom Hals
articles.description: A Missouri jury ordered Bayer (BAYGn.DE) to pay $1.56 billion to four plaintiffs who claimed the company's Roundup weedkiller caused injuries including cancer, a verdict that could intensify investor pressure on the German drugs and agricultural chemicals company to change its legal strategy.
articles.title: Bayer ordered to pay $1.56 billion in latest US trial loss over Roundup weedkiller

articles.author: Nicolás Misculin, Walter Bianchi
articles.description: Argentina was on tenterhooks on Sunday as voting ended in a tight presidential runoff, with two starkly different visions for the country's future on offer and an electorate simmering with anger at triple-digit inflation and rising poverty.
articles.title: Argentina voting ends in nail-biter election with libertarian slight favorite

articles.author: Dan Williams
articles.description: Israel stepped up accusations of Hamas abuses at the Gaza Strip's biggest hospital on Sunday, saying a captive soldier had been executed and two foreign hostages held at a site that has been a focus of its devastating six-week-old offensive.
articles.title: Israel says soldier executed, foreign hostages held at Gaza's Shifa hospital

articles.author: Greg Bensinger
articles.description: The CEO of General Motors' robot-taxi unit Cruise, Kyle Vogt, has resigned from the company a day after apologizing to staff as the company undergoes a safety review of its U.S. fleet.
articles.title: GM's cruise CEO resigns from company - email
